> All,
>=20
> We are re-igniting the next chapter of our Llandover neighborhood View Pr=
eservation efforts. The attached document covers the following:
>=20
> - What view preservation in Llandover means in our CC&Rs
> - Role of the HOA's View Preservation Committee (VPC)
> - The 2015 era View Corridors plan and definitions
> - The process and recommendations for homeowners in a View Corridor
> - Neighbor referrals for local tree services
>=20
> In the coming weeks, we will host an optional lunch & learn call with Tre=
e Solutions (who created the 2015 View Corridors Plan) on what has changed =
since, best practices, and considerations for view preservation work (with =
Q&A of course). Keep a lookout for the invitation.
>=20
> To connect with neighbors in your view corridors (as interested), please =
refer to the neighborhood directory attached and utilize the recommended pr=
ocess.=20
>=20
> As outlined in the document, please reach out to VPC committee member Rho=
nda Gallagher (rlg.seattleme@gmail.com <mailto:rlg.seattleme@gmail.com>) if=
 you will be doing view preservation work in your corridor so that we can u=
nderstand what work is in progress in the neighborhood and, as you need it,=
 help.
>=20
> Please reach out if you have any questions (to those in CC:).
>=20
> Your Llandover VPC,
> Rhonda, Anne & John + HOA President Matt
